PyGyro
======

PyGyro is a Python library for parallel gyro-kinetic simulations.


Installation
============

This project requires parallel h5py. The commands to install this are as follows:

```
export CC=mpicc
export HDF5_MPI="ON"
export HDF5_DIR=$HDF5_HOME

pip install --no-binary=h5py h5py
```

On a module based system the following modules must first be loaded:

```
module load impi
module load anaconda/3
module load mpi4py
module load hdf5-mpi
```

Pyccel
======

If pyccel is installed then the shared object libraries can be created using the command

```
bash buildLibraries.sh
```
